  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A deeply personal mixed-media drawing by **Marlene Dumas** (b. 1953, Cape Town), made in 1989 during the final days of her pregnancy with her daughter **Helena** (born 11 April 1989). The work shows Dumas' heavily pregnant body in a deliberately raw, unromanticized manner — a programmatic subversion of the idealized mother-and-child imagery that dominates the rest of Teylers' Old Master collection. Dumas is widely regarded as **one of the most important living figurative painters**. In May 2025, her painting *Miss January* sold at Christie's for **$13.63 million** — the record for the most expensive work by a living woman artist at auction. In November 2025, she became the **first contemporary woman artist to enter the Louvre's permanent collection**.",
